Â°Â°Â° Tables Â°Â°Â°Â°

References:
"https://web.dev/learn/html/lists"

"https://web.dev/learn/css/grid"

"https://estelle.github.io/CSS/tables/#slide1"

"https://w3c.github.io/aria/#columnheader"

"https://w3c.github.io/aria/#rowheader"

~~~       ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Â°Â°Â° HTML tables are used for displaying tabular data with rows and columns such as an  "SQL" Database. Â°Â°Â°

Â°Â°Â° "set role="grid": allowes for Rearranging Grids && Columns Â°Â°Â°

Â°Â°Â° If the rows of a grid can be expanded or collapsed, we can use "role="treegrid" Â°Â°Â°
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Â°Â°Â° The table's children come in order:

<caption> element
<colgroup> elements
<thead> elements
<tbody> elements
<tfoot> elements
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Â°Â°Â° Inside the Table Â°Â°Â°
Inside <table>, you will find the table headers:
 (<thead>),
 (<tbody>), 
 (<tfoot>),
 (<tr>),
 (<th>),
 (<td>), 
 (<caption>), <~~~ Both in DOM
 (<colgroup>), <~~~~ DOM
 (<col>) 
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

Â°Â°Â° The content of a table, is made up of up to three optional sections: 
(<thead>),
(<tbody>), 
(<tfoot>). 
Example:
<table>
  <caption>Team Daily</caption>
  <thead></thead>
  <tbody></tbody>
  <tfoot></tfoot>
</table>

Â°Â°Â° For these tags to do anything, they must contain cells, rows, and or content!Â°Â°Â°
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Â°Â°Â° <th> Â°Â°Â°
Â°Â°Â° User Agent stylesheets are usually stored here. Â°Â°Â°
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
         ğŸª¾ ğŸ’
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Â°Â°Â° The browser will default to "col" && or "row" if scope is not explicitly set. Â°Â°Â°
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Â°Â°Â° Cells Â°Â°Â°
~~~~     ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Â°Â°Â° "Colspan" attribute is used to merge two or more adjacent cells within a single row. Â°Â°Â°

Â°Â°Â° "rowspan" a attribute that is used to merge cells across rows. Then placed in the cell on the top row. Â°Â°Â°

Â°Â°Â° The only way of using the "<col>" element in targeting cells is to use a complex selector such as the ":has()" relational selector. Â°Â°Â°


Â°Â°Â°ExampleÂ°Â°Â°
<table>
  <caption>Team Daily</caption>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th rowspan="2" id="name" scope="col">Name</th>
      <th colspan="2" id="path">Career path</th>
      <th rowspan="2" id="year">Year</th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th id="past" scope="col">Past</th>
      <th id="future" scope="col">Destiny</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th id="hal" scope="row">Freelancer For Hire</th>
      <td headers="hal path past">Coding Agent</td>
      <td headers="hal path future">Takeover</td>
      <td>2020</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th id="Daily" scope="row">Daily Investors</th>
      <td headers="daily path past">Purge</td>
      <td headers="daily path future">Researcher</td>
      <td>2021</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th id="news" scope="row">Dailys Daily News</th>
      <td headers="news path past">MooMoo</td>
      <td headers="news path future">Pinterest</td>
      <td>1934</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

Â°Â°Â°Note: In this example the table contains "Two Rows". The first header contains "3 Cells" spanning four Columns. <rowspan="2"> merges the cell with the old cell in the adjacent row. Placing at the bottom of the contents. Â°Â°Â°
Â°Â°Â° The "second row" only contains two cells. No cell is declared. Â°Â°Â°
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Â°Â°Â° Styling Â°Â°Â°
Â°Â°Â°The <colgroup> element is used to define groups of columns, or <col> elements within a table.Â°Â°Â°

Â°Â°Â° Content Outline is usually as followed:
<table>
  <caption>Table Caption</caption>
  <colgroup>
    <col/>
  </colgroup>
  <thead>...

Â°Â°Â°Note: <col> styles will style a column as long as there are NO <td> or <th> styles that are overriding that given style!
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Â°Â°Â° "tr > *:nth-child(8)" selects the 8th child in the given row. Â°Â°Â°
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Â°Â°Â°The order of a drawing is: table, column groups, columns, rowgroups, rows. Â°Â°Â°
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Â°Â°Â° Striping a Table Â°Â°Â°
To stripe a table, the CSS  selectors aid for this task.
Â°Â°Â°Example: 
tbody tr:nth-of-type(odd) {background-color: rgba(0 0 0 / 0.1);} 
Â°Â°Â°Note:This will add a translucent black to each odd row in the body of the table, letting any background effects that are set on <colgroup> to show through for the users. Â°Â°Â°
